==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Ambages
<hw>Am*ba"ges</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[L.
(usually in pl.); pref. <ets>ambi-</ets>, <ets>amb-</ets> +
<ets>agere</ets> to drive: cf. F. <ets>ambage</ets>.]</ety> <def>A
circuit; a winding. Hence: Circuitous way or proceeding; quibble;
circumlocution; indirect mode of speech.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>After many <qex>ambages</qex>, perspicuously define what this
melancholy is.</q> <rj><qau>Burton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ambaginous</ent>⟦br⟧
